<FONT SIZE=+1><a href=http://www.casus-belli.net><FONT COLOR=9400D3><b>-Casus Belli; Ayonae Ro-</b></FONT></a><FONT SIZE=-6></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uazndailow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AznDailow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/17/02 5:14:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> From my understanding, any class can learn spells. While not all classes will necessarily cast spells well (expect a lot of failures), it's possible.<br>
<br>
All scrolls you find are only good for one use. Normal spells are found in the same place you select your scrolls from. They'll have a separate header, just named &quot;Spells&quot; IIRC. Right click, and it's in the right hand window under the map I think.<br>
<br>
You also have to buy the spells first from a few different NPCs. Also, with the spellmaker, you can't make a spell with a certain effect, unless you already have the basic spell in your spellbook. Basically, that means you can't make a spell/enchantment with the effect &quot;Damage Health&quot; unless you already own a spell that does that.<br>
<br>
Now, innate spell effects can be found, but only on weapons/armor I believe. If you play a Wood Elf, you'll have an icon down there that acts like a Resist Disease buff. If you follow the main storyline, you'll get a few more buffs there, but the majority come from weapons/armor. Oh, and the enchanted armor/weapons have to have a &quot;Constant Effect&quot;, not casts when used, or casts on striking. If you get the Wraithguard artifact, for example, it gives you a few constant effects of resisting various forms of magic. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubiggins.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Biggins</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elite Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/17/02 5:18:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Thanks.<br>
